    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The day following Friday and preceding Sunday, traditionally regarded as the seventh day of the week, but now frequently considered as the sixth, and, together with Sunday, forming the weekend. Name refers to the Roman Saturn’s-day.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
